                "The Bureau proposed a technical change to \u00a7\u20091026.36(c)(2). Section 1026.36(b) provides that \u00a7\u20091026.36(c)(2) applies to closed-end consumer credit transactions secured by a consumer's principal dwelling. However, current \u00a7\u20091026.36(c)(2) refers to consumer credit transactions secured by a consumer's principal dwelling without referring to closed-end transactions. Consistent with \u00a7\u20091026.36(b), proposed \u00a7\u20091026.36(c)(2) modified the existing language to refer directly to closed-end consumer credit transactions secured by a consumer's principal dwelling.",
                "The Bureau did not receive comments addressing the proposed technical change to \u00a7\u20091024.36(c)(2) and is finalizing as proposed. Accordingly, final \u00a7\u20091024.36(c)(2) refers directly to a closed-end consumer credit transaction secured by a consumer's principal dwelling."
